National Security Advisor Robert O'Brien led the US delegation in commemorating the 60th anniversary of the signing of the OECD convention. O'Brien delivered remarks, participated in panels on COVID-19 recovery, and held bilateral meetings with member states. He reaffirmed the US commitment to the organization and its principles, including free markets, fair trade, investment, innovation, fighting corruption, and the rule of law. O'Brien also advocated for Chris Liddell to become the next Secretary General of the OECD.